---
import BaseLayout from '../../src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const post = {
	title: 'How to Choose Sports Lockers: Complete 2025 Buying Guide',
	description:
		'Complete 2025 buying guide: sizing, materials, customization, and budget for sports lockers. Make the right choice for your facility. 30+ years. Free consultation.',
	category: 'Buying Guides',
	datePublished: '2025-01-20',
	readTime: '9 min read',
	author: 'PlayerStall Editorial Team',
	slug: 'how-to-choose-sports-lockers-2025',
	wordCount: 2000
};

const faqItems = [
	{
		question: 'What locker width should I choose for my sport?',
		answer:
			'Standard widths: 12" for minimal storage, 15" for most sports, 18" for football and hockey with heavy equipment, 24" for premium maximum storage. Consider your sport\'s equipment—football and hockey typically need 18" minimum; basketball can use 15".'
	},
	{
		question: 'Wood vs metal lockers—which is better long-term?',
		answer:
			'Wood lockers offer 15-20 year lifespan, unlimited customization, modular repair, no rust, and premium aesthetic. Metal lockers have lower initial cost but are prone to dents and rust, limited customization, and 10-15 year lifespan. For long-term installations and custom branding, wood delivers better value.'
	},
	{
		question: 'How do I choose the right product tier?',
		answer:
			'Semi Pro ($349) suits high schools and budget-conscious facilities. Varsity ($449) is most popular for collegiate programs. Pro ($549) for professional and elite programs. Stadium ($599) for championship-caliber facilities. All tiers include full 3/4" Birch construction and lifetime guarantee.'
	}
];

const structuredData = {
	'@context': 'https://schema.org',
	'@graph': [
		{
			'@type': 'Article',
			headline: post.title,
			description: post.description,
			datePublished: post.datePublished,
			dateModified: post.datePublished,
			wordCount: post.wordCount,
			author: { '@type': 'Organization', name: post.author },
			publisher: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'PlayerStall', logo: { '@type': 'ImageObject', url: 'https://playerstall.com/images/logoblack2.png' } },
			mainEntityOfPage: { '@type': 'WebPage', '@id': `https://playerstall.com/blog/${post.slug}` }
		},
		{ '@type': 'FAQPage', mainEntity: faqItems.map((item) => ({ '@type': 'Question', name: item.question, acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: item.answer } })) }
	]
};
---

<BaseLayout title={post.title + ' | PlayerStall'} description={post.description}>
	<section class="page-header">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="article-meta">
				<span class="blog-date">January 20, 2025 · {post.readTime}</span>
				<span class="blog-category">{post.category}</span>
			</div>
			<h1>{post.title}</h1>
			<p class="lede">
				Everything you need to know to make the right choice for your athletic facility. From sizing to materials to customization, this comprehensive guide covers it all.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="blog-section">
		<div class="container">
			<article class="blog-content">
				<h2 id="introduction">Introduction: Making the Right Choice</h2>
				<p>Choosing sports lockers is one of the most important decisions you'll make for your athletic facility. The right lockers can enhance team culture, improve organization, and last for decades. The wrong choice can lead to constant maintenance issues, poor functionality, and wasted budget.</p>
				<p>This guide walks you through every factor to consider, from initial planning to final installation.</p>

				<h2 id="step-1">Step 1: Determine Your Space Requirements</h2>
				<h3>Measure Your Locker Room</h3>
				<p>Before choosing lockers, you need accurate measurements:</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Room dimensions:</strong> Length, width, and ceiling height</li>
					<li><strong>Number of athletes:</strong> Current team size plus 10-20% for growth</li>
					<li><strong>Equipment storage needs:</strong> Sport-specific requirements</li>
					<li><strong>Traffic flow:</strong> Entry/exit points and walkways</li>
				</ul>

				<h3>Standard Locker Sizes</h3>
				<p>Most sports lockers come in standard widths:</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>12 inches:</strong> Minimal storage, tight spaces</li>
					<li><strong>15 inches:</strong> Standard for most sports</li>
					<li><strong>18 inches:</strong> Football, hockey with heavy equipment</li>
					<li><strong>24 inches:</strong> Premium, maximum storage</li>
				</ul>

				<h2 id="step-2">Step 2: Choose the Right Material</h2>
				<h3>Wood Sports Lockers</h3>
				<p><strong>Best for:</strong> Long-term installations, custom branding, premium facilities</p>
				<p><strong>Advantages:</strong></p>
				<ul>
					<li>Unlimited customization (colors, logos, names)</li>
					<li>15-20 year lifespan</li>
					<li>Modular repair system</li>
					<li>Premium aesthetic</li>
					<li>No rust or corrosion</li>
				</ul>

				<h3>Metal Sports Lockers</h3>
				<p><strong>Best for:</strong> Tight budgets, temporary installations</p>
				<p><strong>Considerations:</strong></p>
				<ul>
					<li>Lower initial cost</li>
					<li>Prone to dents and rust</li>
					<li>Limited customization</li>
					<li>10-15 year lifespan</li>
				</ul>

				<h2 id="step-3">Step 3: Select Your Product Tier</h2>
				<p>Our lockers come in five tiers, each designed for different needs and budgets:</p>

				<h3>Semi Pro - $349</h3>
				<p><strong>Best for:</strong> High schools, youth programs, budget-conscious facilities</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Full 3/4" Birch wood construction</li>
					<li>Lifetime guarantee</li>
					<li>Basic customization available</li>
				</ul>

				<h3>Varsity - $449</h3>
				<p><strong>Best for:</strong> Collegiate programs, most popular choice</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Enhanced storage capacity</li>
					<li>Premium customization options</li>
					<li>Perfect for recruiting</li>
				</ul>

				<h3>Pro - $549</h3>
				<p><strong>Best for:</strong> Professional teams, elite programs</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Maximum customization</li>
					<li>Professional-grade materials</li>
					<li>Elite appearance</li>
				</ul>

				<h3>Stadium - $599</h3>
				<p><strong>Best for:</strong> Championship-caliber programs</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Ultimate customization package</li>
					<li>Premium hardware</li>
					<li>Maximum storage</li>
				</ul>

				<h2 id="step-4">Step 4: Consider Sport-Specific Needs</h2>
				<h3>Football Lockers</h3>
				<p>Require extra space for helmets, pads, and cleats. Consider 18" width minimum.</p>

				<h3>Hockey Lockers</h3>
				<p>Need ventilation for wet equipment and space for sticks. <a href="/products/accessories">Hockey stick racks</a> are essential.</p>

				<h3>Basketball Lockers</h3>
				<p>Can use standard 15" width. Focus on shoe storage and uniform hanging.</p>

				<h2 id="step-5">Step 5: Plan Your Customization</h2>
				<p>Customization options include:</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Team colors:</strong> Match exact school/team colors</li>
					<li><strong>Logos:</strong> Inlaid, painted, or routed</li>
					<li><strong>Player names:</strong> Engraved on doors</li>
					<li><strong>Number plates:</strong> Custom numbering systems</li>
				</ul>

				<h2 id="step-6">Step 6: Budget Planning</h2>
				<p>Consider total cost of ownership, not just initial price:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Initial purchase price</li>
					<li>Installation costs</li>
					<li>Maintenance over 15 years</li>
					<li>Repair and replacement costs</li>
				</ul>

				<h2 id="step-7">Step 7: Installation Considerations</h2>
				<p>Professional installation ensures:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Proper alignment and spacing</li>
					<li>Secure mounting</li>
					<li>Correct ventilation</li>
					<li>Warranty compliance</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>Conclusion: Making Your Decision</h2>
				<p>Choosing sports lockers is a significant investment. Take time to consider all factors: space, material, tier, sport-specific needs, customization, and long-term costs. When in doubt, consult with experts who have 30+ years of experience.</p>

				<div class="inline-cta">
					<h3>Need Help Choosing?</h3>
					<p>Get a free custom design consultation. Our experts will help you choose the perfect lockers for your facility.</p>
					<a class="btn-secondary" href="/contact">Get Free Consultation</a>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-section" id="faq">
					<h2>Buying Guide FAQ</h2>
					{faqItems.map((item) => (
						<div class="faq-item">
							<h3 class="faq-question">{item.question}</h3>
							<p class="faq-answer">{item.answer}</p>
						</div>
					))}
				</div>
			</article>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="cta-section">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="cta-content">
				<h2>Ready to Choose Your Lockers?</h2>
				<p>Get a free custom design consultation and let our experts guide you.</p>
				<a class="btn-primary" href="/contact">Get Free Consultation</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(structuredData)} />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	:global(:root) { --bg-off-white: #f9f7f2; --border-color: #e3dfd7; --text-gray: #4a4a4a; --accent-color: #fe5900; --text-white: #ffffff; }
	.container { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 1.5rem; }
	.page-header { background: var(--bg-off-white); padding: 4rem 0; text-align: center; }
	.article-meta { display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--accent-color); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
	.page-header h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.25; }
	.lede { max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--text-gray); line-height: 1.8; }
	.blog-section { padding: 4rem 0; }
	.blog-content { background: var(--bg-off-white); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 3rem; }
	.blog-content h2 { margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-size: 2rem; }
	.blog-content h2:first-of-type { margin-top: 0; }
	.blog-content h3 { margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-size: 1.35rem; }
	.blog-content p, .blog-content ul { color: var(--text-gray); font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
	.blog-content ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
	.blog-content li + li { margin-top: 0.5rem; }
	.blog-content a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: none; }
	.blog-content a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
	.inline-cta { background: var(--accent-color); padding: 2.5rem; border-radius: 12px; color: var(--text-white); text-align: center; margin: 3rem 0; }
	.inline-cta h3 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.75rem; color: var(--text-white); }
	.inline-cta p { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.92); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
	.btn-secondary, .btn-primary { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; padding: 0.9rem 2rem; border-radius: 999px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease; }
	.btn-secondary { background: var(--text-white); color: var(--accent-color); }
	.btn-primary { background: var(--accent-color); color: var(--text-white); }
	.btn-secondary:hover, .btn-primary:hover { transform: translateY(-1px); box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.15); }
	.cta-section { background: #121212; color: #fff; padding: 4rem 0; margin-top: 2rem; }
	.cta-content { text-align: center; background: #1f1f1f; padding: 3rem; border-radius: 16px; box-shadow: 0 20px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.25); }
	.cta-content h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 2.25rem; color: #fff; }
	.cta-content p { color: #d8d8d8; margin-bottom: 2rem; font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; }
	.faq-section { margin-top: 3rem; }
	.faq-item { border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 10px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; background: #fff; }
	.faq-question { font-weight: 600; color: #222; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
	.faq-answer { margin: 0.75rem 0 0; }
	@media (max-width: 768px) { .article-meta { flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; } .blog-content { padding: 2rem; } .inline-cta, .cta-content { padding: 2rem; } }
</style>
